The ex-situ BM is based on the catabolic reaction between H2 and CO2 (molar ratio 4:1) that are converted into CH4 (Eq. 1). Additionally, CO2 serves as a carbon source for anabolic reaction of microbial growth that changes the molar ratio to ca. 3.7:1 (Eq. 2) when both anabolism and catabolism are accounted. However, the theoretical uptake for anabolic reaction is minor compared to catabolic reaction (Dupnock and Deshusses 2017). It has been found by Martin et al. (2013) that the experimental growth rate of hydrogenotrophic methanogen (Methanothermobacter thermautotrophicus) was lower than theoretical.1CO2+4H2→CH4+2H2O\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
