The TBR for ex-situ BM offers many advantages compared to different configurations. However, the difficulties regarding several issues were previously reported. The most common difficulties are related to the establishment of archaea in the TBR that leads to a non-efficient CH4 production or acetate synthesis (homoacetogenesis) (Eq. 4) (Logroño et al. 2020). The acetate accumulation was previously reported by e.g., Kougias et al. (2017). The acetate synthesis during the process leads to the pH decrease and lower CH4 production. Therefore, the appropriate operational conditions are critical to manage microbiota towards selective CH4 production.42CO2+4H2→CH3COOH+2H2O\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
